Welcome to Movieola!

	MOVIEOLA is a fully functional, low-cost modeling and 
photo-real rendering system from Radiance Software.

This is a "preview" copy of Movieola. In "preview" mode, you
will be able to preview the interface and texture map a default
object created using Movieola's intuitive "Potter" tool. You can
manipulate the default object's section and profile inside the 
"Potter" tool.  You will also be able to view a series of rendered 
images all created using Movieola.

On-line "on context" help is always enabled in "preview" mode. If
you find this help dialog box popping up a little irritating, you
may want to push the help window behind the main Movieola window.

If you would like to use all the other Movieola tools, you will have
to obtain an evaluation license or a fully functional license for
Movieola. You can do so by calling Radiance Technical Support at
(510) 848-7621 or by sending e-mail to support@radiance.com.

To run Movieola from your CDROM, just go into the 'Movieola' folder 
(if you are not already there) and double-click on 'Movieola'.

To install Movieola on your machine, copy the 'Movieola' folder to a 
convenient location on your disk. To run Movieola, go into the 'Movieola' 
folder, and run the 'Movieola' script there. (The program will run faster 
if you install it on your machine. But make sure you have about 13 Meg of 
free disk space).


